deepDive:{title:"рҹ‘ЁвҖҚрҹ‘©вҖҚрҹ‘§вҖҚрҹ‘Ұ Family & Names in Arabic",body:"Arabic names often tell a family story:\n\nШЈШЁЩҲ (Abu) = 'father of' вҖ” men are often called by their eldest son's name: Abu Mohammed = 'Father of Mohammed'\nШЈЩ… (Umm) = 'mother of' вҖ” same pattern: Umm Khalid = 'Mother of Khalid'\nШ§ШЁЩҶ/ШЁЩҶ (Ibn/Bin) = 'son of' вҖ” used in full names: Mohammed bin Salman = 'Mohammed son of Salman'\n\nThe Arabic word for 'family' (Ш№Ш§ШҰЩ„Ш©) shares a root with 'support' (Ш№Ш§Щ„) вҖ” family means those who support you.\n\nPro tip: If someone tells you 'ШЈЩҶШ§ ШЈШЁЩҲ Ш®Ш§Щ„ШҜ' (I'm Abu Khalid), calling them by this name shows cultural respect!"}
